list.abstract: own是一个英语单词，可以用作名词、动词和形容词，可以翻译为承认、拥有，等等。

yingyinNormal.en: They'd eat their own children.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们连自己的孩子都吃。

yingyinNormal.en: You killed your own men, Viktor.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你杀了自己的士兵，维克多。

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa has made her own television.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩佩做了她自己的电视。

yingyinNormal.en: Why do we like the smell of our own farts?
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么我们喜欢自己的臭屁呢？

yingyinNormal.en: I'm starting my own firm. When? Next week.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我打算开家自己的律所。什么时候? 下周。

yingyinNormal.en: Suddenly I wish I was reading my own name.
yingyinNormal.zh: 突然间，我希望自己的名字在上面。

yingyinNormal.en: Now they are building their own space station.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而如今，他们正在建立他们自己的空间站。

yingyinNormal.en: I mean this is like reading about my own life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就像是读我自己的生活。

yingyinNormal.en: Ariq is a dog. That would eat its own afterbirth.
yingyinNormal.zh: 阿里不哥是条狗，他残害自己的同胞。

yingyinNormal.en: In 2002, Elon Musk started his own rocket company.
yingyinNormal.zh: 埃隆马斯克在2002年开办了他自己的火箭公司。

yingyinNormal.en: The snake that eats its own tail, forever and ever.
yingyinNormal.zh: 蛇吞吃自己的尾巴，无休无止。

yingyinNormal.en: Her own? Oh, yeah. Yeah. No, she's really old-fashioned.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是她自己的孩子？对，不，她真的很传统。

yingyinNormal.en: Spock. You are fully capable of deciding your own destiny.
yingyinNormal.zh: 斯波克，你完全能够决定自己的命运。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, what if he buys his own desk? Yeah, what if I buy my own desk?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，那他出钱买自己的桌子呢？是啊，要是我买我自己的桌子呢？

yingyinNormal.en: So you all have the power in your own way to develop your own Angel Network.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因此，你们每个人都有能力打造自己的天使网络项目。

yingyinNormal.en: I thought you were bringing your own bowling shoes. These are my own bowling shoes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不是要带自己的保龄球鞋来吗？这双就是我自己的啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I just needed to get out on my own, live my own life. And I did, and it's great.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只是想靠自己站起来，过自己的生活，我这么做了，真的很棒。

yingyinNormal.en: Doctor Hamster has picked her own pet to win the prize. That's not fair. It's your own pet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 仓鼠兽医选择了他自己的宠物获得了比赛的奖励。那样不公平。他是你自己的宠物。

yingyinNormal.en: Really? Like what? Well, okay, you're a, you're a talented artist, you own your own business.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真的? 比如说? 好吧你看，你是个才华横溢的艺术家，你有自己的事业。

yingyinNormal.en: We each have our own coat hooks. This one is for you, Emily. Emily is hanging her coat on her very own coat hook.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们每个人都有自己的挂钩。这是给你用的，艾米丽。艾米丽把衣服挂在了她的挂钩上。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

word_family.mean: v. 拥有；有；承认；彻底击败；彻底羞辱；为…承担全责；承认为…负全责；承认是…的父母

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 凭自身的条件；凭自身的力量
充分发挥作用；被充分使用；被充分认可

sense_info_list.en: used to emphasize that something belong to or is connected with somebody

examination_example.sentence: Other companies including Amazon and Disney had also pledged to create their <highlight>own</highlight> plans.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 包括亚马逊和迪士尼在内的其他公司也承诺制定自己的计划。

examination_example.sentence: Both apps, however, were later scrapped, after Microsoft said it had used their best features in its <highlight>own</highlight> products.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，这两个应用程序后来都被废弃了，因为微软表示，它在自己的产品中使用了它们最好的功能。

examination_example.sentence: Companies can also optimize their <highlight>own</highlight> energy use and cut down on the cost of electricity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 公司也可以优化自己的能源使用，降低电力成本。

examination_example.sentence: It may be that the value of Whole Foods to Amazon is not so much the 460 shops it <highlight>owns</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对亚马逊来说，全食超市的价值可能并不在于它拥有的460家门店。

examination_example.sentence: A few wealthy people will <highlight>own</highlight> all the capital, and the masses will struggle in an impoverished wasteland.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 少数富人将拥有全部资本，群众将在一片贫困的荒地上挣扎。

examination_example.sentence: Except in the District of Columbia, non-lawyers may not <highlight>own</highlight> any share of a law firm.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 除了在哥伦比亚特区，非律师不得拥有律师事务所的任何股份。

sense_info_list.en: unaccompanied by others; alone or unaided
sense_info_list.zh: (on one's own)独自地; 独立地

examination_example.sentence: The measures cities must employ when left to tackle dirty air on their <highlight>own</highlight> are politically contentious.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 城市在独自解决空气污染问题时必须采取的措施在政治上有争议。

examination_example.sentence: I can't afford to pay my monthly mortgage payments on my <highlight>own</highlight>, so I have to rent rooms out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我自己付不起每月的抵押贷款，所以我不得不把房间租出去。

examination_example.sentence: No homework should be assigned that students cannot complete on their <highlight>own</highlight> or that they cannot do without expensive equipment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不应该布置学生不能独立完成或没有昂贵设备不能完成的家庭作业。

sense_info_list.en: become fully effective, used, or recognized

examination_example.sentence: When amplifying age and sex differences became a dominant children's marketing strategy, that pink fully came into its <highlight>own</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当放大年龄和性别差异成为儿童市场的主导策略时，粉色完全有了自己的一席之地。

sense_info_list.zh: 彻底击败; 彻底羞辱

word_usage.usage: own作形容词时，不能用在冠词a/an/the之后，可以说I need my own room，但不能说I need an own room.
own作动词，表示“拥有，有”时，不用于进行时。

examination_example.sentence: At the same time, we recognize that children might have an interest in entering adulthood free to create their <highlight>own</highlight> digital footprint.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与此同时，我们认识到，孩子们可能有兴趣在成年后自由地创造他们自己的数字足迹。

examination_example.sentence: "I'd much prefer to have my data used by the maximum number of people to ask their <highlight>own</highlight> questions, " she says.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她说：“我更愿意让尽可能多的人使用我的数据来问自己的问题。”。

examination_example.sentence: A battery-powered world comes with its <highlight>own</highlight> risks, too.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 电池驱动的世界也有其自身的风险。

examination_example.sentence: I want to continue ahead with this dream of <highlight>owning</highlight> my own business.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我想继续实现拥有自己企业的梦想。

examination_example.sentence: It looks like it-after all, 2012 was the tipping point when more than half of Americans began <highlight>owning</highlight> smart phones.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 看起来是这样的——毕竟，2012年是一个转折点，超过一半的美国人开始拥有智能手机。

examination_example.sentence: For example, when you <highlight>own</highlight> something, you view it as more valuable than when you don't <highlight>own</highlight> it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，当你拥有某样东西时，你认为它比你不拥有它时更有价值。

word_usage.usage: own作“拥有”解时是及物动词，不必再加其他介词。

examination_example.sentence: They will care less about their <highlight>own</highlight> background.

examination_example.sentence: These days you'd be hard pressed to find anyone in Australia over the age of 15 who doesn't <highlight>own</highlight> a mobile phone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如今，你很难在澳大利亚找到15岁以上但没有手机的人。

examination_example.sentence: He had <highlight>owned</highlight> that business for 15 years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他拥有那家企业已经15年了。

examination_example.sentence: Anneke helps her students get over the fear and create their <highlight>own</highlight> animation works.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Anneke帮她的学生克服恐惧，创作他们自己的动画作品。

examination_example.sentence: To begin with, I'd like to tell a story from my <highlight>own</highlight> life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首先，我想成为一名消防员，消防员的制服看起来很酷。

examination_example.sentence: Today I am living a creative life as the designer of my <highlight>own</highlight> fashion brand.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 现在，作为自己的时尚品牌设计师，我过着富有创造力的生活。

word_usage.usage:
own只用于形容词性物主代词或名词所有格后：
I won't believe it unless I see it with my own eyes.
除非我亲眼看见，否则我是不会相信的。
名词后可以用of one's own作定语：
I’ll settle the problem in a way of my own.
我会用自己的方式解决这个问题。

examination_example.sentence: It's a good thing to have different friends with different opinions because you can each share your <highlight>own</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 拥有持不同观点的不同朋友是一件好事，因为你们每个人都可以分享自己的观点。

examination_example.sentence: Young people are encouraged to work hard to achieve their <highlight>own</highlight> dreams.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 鼓励年轻人为实现自己的梦想而努力工作。

examination_example.sentence: I think it's important to be independent (独立的) and make my <highlight>own</highlight> choices.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我认为独立并做出自己的选择很重要。

examination_example.sentence: Let us remember that we hold in our hand the most powerful instrument which man <highlight>owns</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 让我们记住，我们手中握着人类拥有的最强大的工具。

examination_example.sentence: The little cars of the future will cost much less money to <highlight>own</highlight> and to drive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 未来小型汽车的购置和驾驶成本将大大降低。

examination_example.sentence: Now, he <highlight>owns</highlight> a coffee company (公司) called 734, which is part of his program.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 现在，他拥有一家名为 734的咖啡公司，这是他计划的一部分。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 最常用词，可指任何情况下的具有，无论是物质的或精神的。
指拥有并保持财产及持有见解等，暗示不让别人拿走或占有。
